Lets Hope This Lives


24 May 2017 16:38






Alright, this is my third skip. Hopefully. Hopefully it works. What was I going for here? Well, originally I had it as an army of woodboring beetles that were destroying a forest god, but that didn't work. Then I focused on making the bugs cuter while having the forest god in the background. In the end, I found out I just liked the bugs, so I removed the forest god altogether. And then I thought, but what do they do? After I figured out their , I realised I didn't have to have them be sapient anymore, so I've left it debatable. I hope I have a good layer of mystery here.

EDIT: Made some last minute revisions, and there is now an addendum that I am proud of. Tell me what y'all think.

EDIT 2: Yay for +40! Is this a big landmark? No! But it's been at +39 for what has felt like forever! So I am glad to not stare at that 9. Taunting me. Thank you, for +40.

EDIT 3: Actually justified yay for +50! Yayy!

Yearsart~!

Yayy!








